  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Hey Jess,

Some feedback on these patches:

* 0001 is great. Thank you for looking into this bug. You chose to use
'linebreaks' rather than 'linebreaksbr'. Elsewhere we use 'linebreaksbr' but
actually I like your way better. For that reason I've switched our other uses to
the 'linebreaks' filter.

* When applying 0002, git gives me an error about "whitespace errors". Some of
your lines end in a space character. Nerdy people all over the Internet seem to
dislike this, but I don't really understand why. I'm glad that you fixed them in
0003. I fixed a few more that were lingering in comments.

So -- cleanup patches are welcome. There isn't a code style document. I haven't
given code style a great deal of explicit thought; the nicest thing would be if
we can just adopt someone else's code style document (-:

---

As for the test failures... yes, um, eeek. Those are known issues in the sense
that I know about them, but we should really fix those failing tests, as they're
decreasing the usefulness of the test suite!

--

I'm marking this as resolved -- I just checked Will's profile, and it does the
spacing properly!</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg625">msg625 (view)</a></th>
